Count 1 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
2) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacy unless agent approves otherwise;
3) Reimburse buy money of $320.00; 
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
7) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination.   
Count 4 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three and one-half (3 1/2) years, concurrent with count 1.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
2) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacy unless agent approves otherwise;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Pay costs of action; 
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
6) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination.  
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program but not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  
Defendant is entitled to 11 days credit.   
Minutes.
